    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/988: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName
                            corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-19T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 19, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 19—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. From the Secretary.<note n="94" xml:id="d67fn94">Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHL1">Stimson</persName> had sailed from New York on the <hi
                            rend="italic">Ile de France</hi>, April 8; he arrived at Havre, April
                        15; and at the Villa Bessinge, Geneva, April 16. He left Geneva, May 1;
                        arrived at New York aboard the <hi rend="italic">Vulcania</hi>, May 14.
                        During this period Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">Castle</persName> was
                        Acting Secretary of State.</note> I have already had conferences with
                        <persName corresp="#p_TAP1">Tardieu</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LP1"
                        >Laval</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BP1">Berthelot</persName> in
                    Paris and with <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_LSWT1">Walter Layton</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BH2"
                        >Bruening</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MT1">Matsudaira</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_RBT1">Tevfik</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MG1"
                        >Motta</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> here.
                    Have discussed disarmament questions, also the Far East, with most of them. On
                    latter subject had particularly satisfactory talks with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BP1">Berthelot</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1"
                        >Simon</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_LSWT1">Layton</persName>. No one
                    raised the question of reparations. Today shall see <persName corresp="#p_GD1"
                        >Grandi</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BH2">Bruening</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_TWCT1">te Water</persName> and
                        <persName>Wilford</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_MJR1"
                        >MacDonald</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HVD1">Hailsham</persName>
                    will arrive Thursday morning. Contrary to my previous information it is now very
                    evident that French cannot do anything definite until after elections May 1st.
                        <persName corresp="#p_TAP1">Tardieu</persName>, however, is coming down this
                    week end to see me and am not without hope that we may make progress towards
                    some ultimate solution. Was very conciliatory in Paris although it was evident
                    that his main preoccupation was his campaign which is very intense. Morale of
                    American delegation high and all working hard. [<persName corresp="#p_SHL1"
                        >Stimson</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
